fields.description: Robots attack us when we least expect it.  Learn how to defend yourself against these mechanical oppressors by taking control of your environment.  Join now, before it's too late.
fields.title: Robots Attack

fields.description: Explore the technology and findings of the mars rover expeditions to the martian surface.  NASA officials from the rover programs answer your questions and more.
fields.title: Robotics on Mars

fields.description: Meet with experts from around the area to discuss advances in practical application of computer vision research.  View demonstrations of the latest hardware implementing the theory.
fields.title: Computer Vision Seminar

fields.description: View a demonstration of the PT-1, the world's first commercially viable jet pack.
fields.title: Jet Pack Demonstration

fields.description: The first launch of the newest generation of spacecraft.  The Ares V will be making the first of four planned flights this year.
fields.title: Constellation Inaugural Launch

fields.description: NASA brings all the astronauts, pilots, scientists, and engineers out to the park and let's them play.  This is a special event in a NASA employee's life, when they turn into adults.
fields.title: Space Week

fields.description: People into space come here and dress up as their favorite space objects.  For example, I will be going as a wormhole.
fields.title: Space Convention

fields.description: Some filler text for the event description.  Sometimes I make things up, but this time I'm just describing the process.
fields.title: Space Related
